-- Bank of Japan May Cut GDP Forecasts Next Month, Yomiuri Shimbun Reports
-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 2010-09-29T22:13:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/bank-of-japan-may-cut-gdp-forecasts-next-month-yomiuri-shimbun-reports.html
The Bank of Japan may cut its
assessment of the economic outlook at a meeting scheduled for
Oct. 28, the Yomiuri newspaper reported, without citing anyone.  The central bank may cut its forecast for fiscal 2010
growth in real gross domestic product to between 2 percent and
2.5 percent, compared with its current 2.6 percent estimate, the
report said. The bank may also cut its outlook for fiscal 2011,
the report said.  The bank may decide on taking additional monetary easing
steps at a policy meeting on Oct. 5, the report said. Measures
may include expanding a low-rate loan facility, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
